headline: Trump-Colombia tensions thaw after months of heated exchanges
description: After threatening and insulting Colombian leader Gustavo Petro, the US president unexpectedly invited him to the White House.

Instead of commenting on the unthinkable, Europeans should take action in Greenland
description: If Europeans allow the US to take control of Greenland, NATO would cease to be an alliance and the European Union would become a protectorate, a group of researchers argues in this op-ed for Le Monde.

headline: Israeli government accelerates settlement expansion in occupied West Bank
description: With tenders for 9,600 housing units for Jewish families in the occupied West Bank, 2025 set a record, with an openly stated goal of delivering 'a fatal blow to the idea of a Palestinian state.'

headline: France enjoys another banner year for tourism, buoyed by campgrounds and international visitors
description: International tourism revenue rose by 9% in France in 2025, according to the United Nations World Tourism Organization.

headline: China's Pingtan Island reflects rising tensions in the Taiwan Strait
description: On Pingtan Island, China's closest point to Taiwan, repeated Chinese military maneuvers are exasperating fishers and fueling 'reunification' tourism.

'If Doctors Without Borders were to cease activities in Gaza, the impact would be absolutely enormous'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, Filipe Ribeiro, head of mission for Doctors Without Borders in Jerusalem, responds to the Israeli government's decision to ban it and 36 other non-governmental organizations from operating in the occupied Palestinian territories.

headline: French judges alarmed by rumors of US sanctioning magistrates who sentenced Le Pen
description: Peimane Ghaleh-Marzban, the president of the Paris judicial court, spoke out to condemn what he called 'unacceptable interference.' His remarks followed revelations in the German press about the possibility that the United States might sanction the French judges who sentenced Marine Le Pen.

headline: Venezuela: How the US spent months preparing the military operation to capture Maduro
description: Images verified by Le Monde made it possible to reconstruct the US's vast military deployment at sea, on land and in the air in the months leading up to the abduction of the Venezuelan president.
